libmicroros cortex-m33 rebuild instructions
============================================

The official prebuilt libmicroros.a targets RP2040 (armv6-m/cortex-m0plus)
and will NOT link on the RP2350 (cortex-m33).  You must rebuild from source.

Prerequisites
-------------
  • Docker
  • git

Steps
-----
1. Clone the pico micro-ROS builder:

     git clone https://github.com/micro-ROS/micro_ros_raspberrypi_pico_sdk /tmp/uros-pico

2. Edit the toolchain to target cortex-m33.  In the cloned repo find
   toolchain.cmake (or the equivalent flags file) and replace:

     -march=armv6-m -mcpu=cortex-m0plus

   with:

     -mcpu=cortex-m33 -mthumb -march=armv8-m.main+fp+dsp \
     -mfloat-abi=softfp -mfpu=fpv5-sp-d16

   IMPORTANT: -mfloat-abi=softfp must match what pico-sdk uses for
   rp2350-arm-s.  Confirm by checking the generated flags.make in your
   Phase-A CMake build directory (build/CMakeFiles/materwelon.dir/flags.make).
   Adjust if the value differs.

3. Run the docker builder:

     cd /tmp/uros-pico
     docker build -t micro-ros-pico-m33 .
     docker run --rm -v $(pwd):/uros_ws micro-ros-pico-m33

4. Copy the artifacts here:

     cp /tmp/uros-pico/libmicroros.a   firmware/libmicroros/
     cp -r /tmp/uros-pico/include      firmware/libmicroros/
     cp /tmp/uros-pico/pico_uart_transport.c  firmware/libmicroros/
     cp /tmp/uros-pico/pico_uart_transport.h  firmware/libmicroros/

5. Build with micro-ROS enabled:

     cmake -DENABLE_MICROROS=ON ..

Known issues
------------
  • GitHub issues #1327 and #1482 in micro-ROS/micro_ros_raspberrypi_pico_sdk
    track RP2350 support.  Check those threads for patches if the build fails.
  • Float-ABI mismatch is the most common link error.  Verify step 2 above
    against the actual pico-sdk flags.
